OL,3,CSwinney admits he cannot guarantee
OL,4,Cchild poverty will continue to reduce
OL,6,F"Essentially, our genuine, focused
OL,7,Fmeasures to reduce child poverty ` and
OL,8,Fwe've obviously demonstrated that we
OL,9,Fcan be successful in that respect `
OL,10,Fagainst a prevailing trend moving in
OL,11,Fthe opposite direction stands to be
OL,12,Fundermined by the actions of the UK
OL,13,FGovernment.
OL,15,F"I suppose the way I would
OL,16,Fcharacterise it is that we will do
OL,17,Feverything we possibly can do, but we
OL,18,Fcan't ignore the prevailing pressure
OL,19,Fand draw of other factors which might
OL,20,Factually make our challenge even
OL,21,Fgreater.
